Package: cryptpilot
Architecture: any
Depends: cryptpilot-fde-host (= ${binary:Version}),
         cryptpilot-fde-guest (= ${binary:Version}),
         cryptpilot-crypt (= ${binary:Version}),
         cryptpilot-verity (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Full-disk encryption and data protection tool for confidential computing
 Cryptpilot is a full-disk encryption utility for protecting data at rest
 in confidential computing environments. This meta-package installs all
 cryptpilot components: cryptpilot-fde-host, cryptpilot-fde-guest, cryptpilot-crypt, and cryptpilot-verity.
 .
 It provides LUKS2-based encryption for rootfs and data volumes, integrates
 with dracut for early-boot decryption, and supports multiple key providers
 including TPM2, KBS (Key Broker Service), KMS, OIDC, OTP, and custom exec plugins.

Package: cryptpilot-fde-host
Architecture: any
Depends: lvm2,
         cryptsetup-bin,
         coreutils,
         kmod,
         util-linux,
         qemu-utils,
         file,
         libguestfs-tools,
         cloud-guest-utils,
         grub2-common,
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: dosfstools,
            xfsprogs,
            e2fsprogs
Suggests: confidential-data-hub,
          attestation-agent
Description: Full-disk encryption host-side tooling (conversion, configuration, reference values)
 Cryptpilot-fde-host provides host-side tools for full-disk encryption management,
 including disk image conversion (cryptpilot-convert), image hardening (cryptpilot-enhance),
 boot artifact reference value computation (show-reference-value), and configuration
 validation (config check/dump).

Package: cryptpilot-fde-guest
Architecture: any
Depends: dracut,
         dracut-network,
         lvm2,
         cryptsetup-bin,
         coreutils,
         systemd,
         kmod,
         util-linux,
         cloud-guest-utils,
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: e2fsprogs
Description: Full-disk encryption guest-side boot service (initrd decryption)
 Cryptpilot-fde-guest provides the boot-service binary that runs during initrd
 to set up encrypted volumes (dm-crypt, dm-verity, LVM, overlayfs) before the
 root filesystem is mounted. This package is designed for inclusion in guest
 disk images and has minimal dependencies.

Package: cryptpilot-crypt
Architecture: any
Depends: cryptsetup-bin,
         coreutils,
         systemd,
         kmod,
         util-linux,
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: dosfstools,
            xfsprogs,
            e2fsprogs,
            confidential-data-hub,
            attestation-agent
Description: Data volume encryption tooling
 Cryptpilot-crypt provides data volume encryption and automatic volume
 management for confidential computing environments.

Package: cryptpilot-verity
Architecture: any
Depends: fuse3,
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Integrity measurement tool for directory trees
 Cryptpilot-verity is an integrity measurement tool for directory trees
 in confidential computing environments.
